## Radius of gyration
The radius of gyration (Rg) is a measure of the spatial distribution of atoms around the molecule’s center of mass, reflecting its compactness and conformational state. It is calculated as the root mean square distance of each atom from the center of mass, weighted by their masses, using the equation30.
